data.chText: 全能的上主，请垂怜我们。
data.enText: Almighty God, have mercy on us.

data.chText: 砰的 / 哗啦 / 轰的一声巨响
（表示惊奇或愤怒）全能的，有无限权力的
data.enText: used in the expressions shown in the example, to express surprise or anger

data.chText: 全能的基督 / 上帝！你认为你究竟在干什么？
data.enText: Christ/God Almighty! What the hell do you think you are doing?

means: (表示惊奇或愤怒)全能的，有无限权力的

value.def: The Almighty is another name for God. You can also refer to Almighty God .

example.ex: Adam sought guidance from the Almighty...
Let us now confess our sins to Almighty God.
example.tran: 现在让我们向上帝忏悔我们的罪恶。

value.tran: 全能者（指上帝）；全能的上帝

value.def: People sometimes say God Almighty or Christ Almighty to express their surprise, anger, or horror. These expressions could cause offence.
value.tran: （表示惊奇、愤怒或恐惧，可能具冒犯意味）上帝呀，耶稣呀

value.def: Almighty means very serious or great in extent.

example.ex: I had the most almighty row with the waitress...
example.tran: 我和女招待大吵了一架。
